TEXT -16 -304 Left 2 ;Summing
TEXT 320 -304 Left 2 ;Integrator 1
TEXT 648 -304 Left 2 ;Integrator 2
TEXT 56 440 Left 2 ;Example design: BP,\nPeakGain = Unity,\nf_center = 5k,\nBW = +/-100Hz -> -3dB\n \nDESIGN: Frequency Scale\nLet all R except R1, R7 = 1ohm. Let all C = 1F.\n \nAv = KQ = R7/R1\n=> For unity gain, set 1/k = Q (R1 = R7)\n \nBW = 200Hz\n=> Q = f_center / BW = 5k / 200 = 25\n \nf_center = 1 / (2piRC)\n=> C = 1/ (2pi * 1ohm * f_center) = 1 / 31.42k = 31.8uF\n \nZ scale by 10k:\nR = 10k\nC = 31.8uF / 10k = 3.18nF\nQ = 25 * 10k = 250k = R7 = 1/k = R1
TEXT 568 216 Left 2 ;R1 = 1/k\nR7 = Q
TEXT -544 280 Left 2 !.ac dec 100 10 100k
TEXT 808 632 Left 2 ;In reality, add bias compensation resistors to In+
